		<h1>Tranquil</h1>

<h2>What is tranquil?</h2>

<p>Tranquil is a light CMS and MVC-based PHP-framework, written from ground-up using secure technologies and open-source solutions.</p>

<p>Tranquil utilizes the tranquil-css-framework, which is freely available on its <a href="http://cdn.dronki.tech/tranquil/css/" target="_blank">CDN-page</a>.</p>

<p>The administration uses <a href="https://ckeditor.com/" target="_blank">CKEditor</a>, and due to this framework being open-source and easy to modify, it&#39;s quite easy to replace CKEditor to <a href="https://www.tinymce.com/download/" target="_blank">TinyMCE</a>.</p>

<p>Pages such as this, can be created using the administration, and all pages supports meta-tags, meta-description, and canonical-URL. Pages can also be set as active (available for all), preview (only available for admins to preview), and inactive (not available to anyone).</p>

<p>This framework also utilizes a template-engine that is written from scratch, so each view can add scripts, stylesheets, and meta-tags on the fly when generating the page.</p>

<h2>Core-functions:</h2>

<ul>
	<li>clConfig.php - for reading and storing variables in the database.</li>
	<li>clDbPDO.php - for communicating with the database.</li>
	<li>clLogger.php - Log important messages from modules to a file.</li>
	<li>clRegistry.php - Instantiate and control instantiated objects from one file.</li>
	<li>clRouter.php - Takes care of all the routing performed in the framework.</li>
	<li>clTableHtml.php - Create tables on the fly.</li>
	<li>clTemplate.php - The template-engine.</li>
	<li>clView.php - View-rendering and scripting-engine.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Models:</h2>

<ul>
	<li>admin - The model responsible for the administration.</li>
	<li>infoContent - The model for inserting and managing the pages that can be displayed.</li>
	<li>moduleInstaller - Not quite done yet.</li>
	<li>navigation - Generates the navigation based on parents, groups, classes, behavior, and prefix-content (such as <a href="https://fontawesome.com/icons?d=gallery" target="_blank">fontawesome</a>)</li>
</ul>

